Cultivar: isolation and growth conditionTo ensure the 100% of emergence rate, all tested seeds were healthy and soaked in water for 24 hours before sowing. The 9 basins of seeds would kept grow in greenhouse for 10 days, with conditions of 14:10 photoperiod and temperature of 281. Then the 9 basins of seedlings were divided into 3 groups, 2 treatments and 1 control would be set as follow: Group 1, for each basin, 300 individuals of 3-4 instars of planthopper nymphs were released and they could freely move and feed on the 30 seedlings for next 24 hours. Then 5 stems of each rice  were cut, put into three cryo tubes and store in a -80  refrigerator rapidly. The tubes were labeled as GH308-IB, HR05-IB and TN1-IB. The tested brown planthoppers were reared indoor for at least 10 generations, feed with seedlings of TN1during their whole life; Group 2, the stems of each seedling would be prick 10 times randomly every hour in next 24 hours, as simulation of insect piercing, then 5 stems of each rice  were cut, put into three cryo tubes and store in a -80  refrigerator rapidly (labeled as GH308-MIB, HR05-MIB and TN1-MIB); Group 3, the last three basins was set as control and treated with nothing. After 24 hours, the stems were collected as above did (labeled as GH308-CK, HR05-CK and TN1-CK)
